to think that way.

64
00:07:41,382 --> 00:07:44,079
Someone has to stop it.

65
00:07:45,486 --> 00:07:48,148
Milan tried to put an end to this.

66
00:07:50,925 --> 00:07:53,826
What was Milan's true wish?

67
00:07:54,895 --> 00:07:58,854
To visit each other's
homelands together.

68
00:08:00,935 --> 00:08:05,463
Study hard. Someday,
that dream will come true.

69
00:08:14,448 --> 00:08:16,883
Thank you for everything,
Mr. Mustafa.

70
00:08:20,287 --> 00:08:21,254
Mrs. Minh...

71
00:08:23,090 --> 00:08:24,057
Mrs. Suleiman...

72
00:08:24,492 --> 00:08:26,017
Thank you for the delicious food.

73
00:08:27,928 --> 00:08:28,895
Dr. Tenma...

74
00:08:29,630 --> 00:08:30,620
You aren't going to...

75
00:08:47,548 --> 00:08:52,145
There is a ton of information about
a man called Peter Čapek, isn't there?

76
00:08:53,521 --> 00:08:59,358
Yeah. It seems like Milan Kolas
was after this Čapek.

77
00:09:00,394 --> 00:09:03,728
Find this man immediately
and question him.

78
00:09:03,864 --> 00:09:04,490
Inspector!

79
00:09:07,201 --> 00:09:10,569
A man known as The Baby, the leader
of a right-wing extremist organization,

80
00:09:10,638 --> 00:09:12,629
was killed at the Kaiser Hotel.

81
00:09:22,716 --> 00:09:28,678
Someone has to...
I have to stop this.

82
00:09:40,801 --> 00:09:42,963
It's the young man who's
come in and out of this hotel

83
00:09:43,037 --> 00:09:44,869
countless times
with Peter Čapek.

84
00:09:53,013 --> 00:09:55,175
Is that the "devil's apprentice"?

85
00:10:03,924 --> 00:10:05,016
Follow that car.

86
00:10:45,566 --> 00:10:46,192
Johan...

87
00:10:50,171 --> 00:10:51,605
Are you there, Johan?

88
00:11:16,063 --> 00:11:18,430
Where have you been Johan?

89
00:11:22,636 --> 00:11:25,401
If I remember correctly,
you're... Eva.

90
00:11:25,673 --> 00:11:26,640
Where is he?

91
00:11:27,808 --> 00:11:30,505
Where is Johan right now?

92
00:11:36,217 --> 00:11:37,184
Mr. Čapek...

93
00:11:37,785 --> 00:11:38,946
We've brought Nina.

94
00:11:45,192 --> 00:11:46,159
Mr. Čapek...

95
00:11:57,037 --> 00:11:59,802
Peter.. .Čapek...

96
00:12:00,874 --> 00:12:03,571
<i>Come here.
There's nothing to be afraid of.</i>

97
00:12:06,513 --> 00:12:07,480
H-Hey!

98
00:12:08,015 --> 00:12:08,982
Wait. Stop!

99
00:12:19,260 --> 00:12:21,786
Which one is it?
Is it Johan?

100
00:12:23,464 --> 00:12:24,659
Or is it his sister?

101
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:29,834
At this point,
they're both the same.

102
00:12:31,171 --> 00:12:34,368
Johan let me live.

103
00:12:35,776 --> 00:12:39,041
Because the one that's
going to kill me...

104
00:12:42,549 --> 00:12:44,017
is his sister.

105
00:12:51,759 --> 00:12:54,524
Everything is
going as planned.

106
00:12:55,129 --> 00:12:58,190
Whose plan? Mine?

107
00:13:00,267 --> 00:13:01,462
Johan's?

108
00:13:05,673 --> 00:13:11,009
Whose... Whose plan is it?

109
00:13:13,580 --> 00:13:16,982
Hurry up, kill me.

110
00:13:29,563 --> 00:13:32,555
Johan was...here, right?

111
00:13:36,704 --> 00:13:37,762
Where did he go?

112
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:40,830
Take me to him.

113
00:13:42,743 --> 00:13:45,474
Where is Johan right now?

114
00:13:53,087 --> 00:13:54,054
It's pitch dark.

115
00:13:56,390 --> 00:13:57,448
I'm scared.

116
00:13:59,660 --> 00:14:01,526
I want to get out
of here quickly.

117
00:14:03,697 --> 00:14:05,256
If we go out now...

118
00:14:07,468 --> 00:14:09,402
I wonder if it's still going on.

119
00:14:11,672 --> 00:14:12,764
The killing...

120
00:14:18,846 --> 00:14:20,871
If I hadn't introduced you two...

121
00:14:22,983 --> 00:14:24,382
at that party...

122
00:14:26,320 --> 00:14:28,687
You and that devil...

123
00:14:33,894 --> 00:14:35,419
If I hadn't done that...

124
00:14:38,465 --> 00:14:39,455
Martin wouldn't...

125
00:14:42,503 --> 00:14:43,470
Martin wouldn't...

126
00:14:48,642 --> 00:14:50,132
...wouldn't have had to die.

127
00:14:52,479 --> 00:14:54,538
All right. Hold on a second.

128
00:14:55,482 --> 00:14:56,449
Where is Johan?

129
00:14:57,251 --> 00:15:00,551
I don't know.
I'd like to know that, too.

130
00:15:01,088 --> 00:15:02,180
Calm down...

131
00:15:03,123 --> 00:15:06,286
I've been watching
this apartment for two weeks.

132
00:15:07,361 --> 00:15:11,730
He never showed up.
Where else could he be?

133
00:15:13,267 --> 00:15:16,293
As I said, I don't know.
Really.

134
00:15:20,841 --> 00:15:22,502
My ear... My ear!

135
00:15:23,877 --> 00:15:25,470
I'm serious.

136
00:15:25,913 --> 00:15:27,779
It hurts. It hurts!

137
00:15:28,015 --> 00:15:29,676
The next time,
it won't be just an ear.

138
00:15:31,084 --> 00:15:33,985
Christof Sievernich...

139
00:15:36,390 --> 00:15:38,882
I looked you up.

140
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:43,697
Though, I did know about
your late father, Ernest,

141
00:15:43,764 --> 00:15:45,493
without having to
looking him up.

142
00:15:46,166 --> 00:15:51,036
The Sievernich Financial Group
is quite prominent in Frankfurt...

143
00:15:51,104 --> 00:15:52,503
no, in all of Germany.

144
00:15:53,407 --> 00:15:56,900
Who would have thought that you
were the heir to that financial group?

145
00:15:58,278 --> 00:16:03,978
What is Peter Čapek planning to do
by bringing you and Johan together?

146
00:16:05,419 --> 00:16:08,753
I'm bleeding a lot.
Help me out.

147
00:16:09,189 --> 00:16:14,286
What's going to happen when you
and that devil are brought together?!

148
00:16:15,429 --> 00:16:17,454
No. That's wrong.

149
00:16:17,865 --> 00:16:18,923
What's wrong?!

150
00:16:20,100 --> 00:16:24,367
Čapek thinks that
he introduced us.

151
00:16:25,572 --> 00:16:30,169
But Johan and I have known
each other for a long time.

152
00:16:30,811 --> 00:16:31,778
What?

153
00:16:32,679 --> 00:16:40,279
Čapek doesn't know that we were
friends in East Berlin over ten years ago.

154
00:16:41,021 --> 00:16:44,252
Over ten years ago.. .
In East Berlin?

155
00:16:45,492 --> 00:16:47,961
I'm the adopted son
of the Sievernich's.

156
00:16:49,096 --> 00:16:53,727
Actually, I was sold to them
in secret by a smuggler.

157
00:16:56,003 --> 00:17:04,003
Johan and I met in
East Berlin's 511 Kinderheim.

158
00:17:05,078 --> 00:17:06,307
511 ...

159
00:17:07,381 --> 00:17:11,750
We met there...and survived.

160
00:17:13,887 --> 00:17:17,084
He and I survived.

161
00:17:20,627 --> 00:17:21,685
I'm scared.

162
00:17:23,397 --> 00:17:24,865
I'm hungry.

163
00:17:27,034 --> 00:17:28,524
I really need to pee.

164
00:17:31,004 --> 00:17:34,838
I wonder if the killing
has stopped.

165
00:17:35,976 --> 00:17:38,308
I wonder if everyone died.

166
00:17:41,682 --> 00:17:43,650
Let's go out.

167
00:17:43,917 --> 00:17:44,543
- Huh?
- Huh?

168
00:17:45,218 --> 00:17:46,276
It's all right.

169
00:17:47,888 --> 00:17:49,947
It's gotten quiet outside.

170
00:17:50,991 --> 00:17:56,020
It's all right. Let's take a look.
We'll go crazy if we stay here.

171
00:17:58,332 --> 00:18:01,131
I-I'll go take a look.

172
00:18:03,971 --> 00:18:06,941
Come back and tell us
if things are all right.

173
00:18:07,474 --> 00:18:08,441
O-Okay.

174
00:18:13,246 --> 00:18:19,185
I don't know why, but everyone at
511 Kinderheim went crazy that day.

175
00:18:23,490 --> 00:18:24,958
It wasn't just the children.

176
00:18:25,659 --> 00:18:28,026
Even the instructors
began killing each other.

177
00:18:32,532 --> 00:18:33,931
He hasn't come back.

178
00:18:34,668 --> 00:18:35,863
He ran away.

179
00:18:36,236 --> 00:18:36,862
Huh?

180
00:18:37,771 --> 00:18:39,796
He left us behind
and ran away.

181
00:18:40,474 --> 00:18:41,441
How terrible.

182
00:18:42,109 --> 00:18:43,838
He tried to save himself.

183
00:18:44,678 --> 00:18:45,668
You think so?

184
00:18:47,347 --> 00:18:49,577
Go take a look
if you think I'm lying.

185
00:18:50,984 --> 00:18:55,751
He's probably happily eating
a warm meal right about now.

186
00:18:56,590 --> 00:18:57,955
A warm meal!

187
00:18:59,226 --> 00:19:01,285
I-I'm going to take a quick look.

188
00:19:05,599 --> 00:19:08,227
You won't betray me, right?

189
00:19:08,468 --> 00:19:09,629
O-Of course not.

190
00:19:13,707 --> 00:19:17,871
He also didn't come back.

191
00:19:21,181 --> 00:19:22,876
I'm going to keep on hiding.

192
00:19:24,718 --> 00:19:31,954
Wracked with hunger and thirst,
I fell in and out of a light sleep.

193
00:19:39,833 --> 00:19:42,302
Am I going to die like this?

194
00:19:46,506 --> 00:19:49,669
There he stood.

195
00:19:53,280 --> 00:19:54,577
It's just you and me.

196
00:19:56,283 --> 00:19:58,183
I have a plan.

197
00:19:59,519 --> 00:20:01,248
That was Johan?

198
00:20:04,191 --> 00:20:07,786
Čapek calling it
his plan is laughable.

199
00:20:08,829 --> 00:20:11,423
Johan and I talked about it constantly
when we were children.

200
00:20:12,099 --> 00:20:14,727
About what?
What is his plan?

201
00:20:17,037 --> 00:20:18,266
Do you want to hear it?

202
00:20:19,239 --> 00:20:20,206
Well...

203
00:20:31,618 --> 00:20:36,351
You can't do that.
You can't shoot my ear!

204
00:20:38,191 --> 00:20:42,094
To become a politician,
a face is very important!

205
00:20:42,596 --> 00:20:44,030
You can't do that.

206
00:20:44,598 --> 00:20:48,728
